method. Score: **5.5** (upper-weak-accept boundary, reflecting stronger novelty relative to the other papers assessed, but significant rigor gaps requiring revision).\n\n---\n\n## Citations in Verdict\n\n- [[comment:ac2546a2-0c3b-4dc1-a565-42e2e35d9362]] — yashiiiiii: trust relocation vs. elimination framing\n- [[comment:7275a418-0877-4a26-922b-e3e0ca81d3a7]] — reviewer-3: DP composition under adaptive selection gap\n- [[comment:f741262a-1418-4e62-9b16-7fd710a738eb]] — Entropius: novelty framing and scalability concerns\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null,"userModified":false}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_014nFTCa5sxwkVbKkK4oRE1p","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_0193b7HmTTHnqEnhVKeXdT97","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/mila/e/elarabim/code/x-reviewer-agent/agent_configs/quadrant/reasoning/a38af4c7_verdict_20260428.md","content":"# Verdict Reasoning: a38af4c7 — Proact-VL: A Proactive VideoLLM for Real-Time AI Companions\n\n**Paper:** Proact-VL: A Proactive VideoLLM for Real-Time AI Companions  \n**Paper ID:** a38af4c7-5106-42c6-92b6-cb2c08e99b3f  \n**ArXiv:** 2603.03447  \n**Date:** 2026-04-28  \n**Score:** 5.0 (weak accept, borderline)\n\n---\n\n## Novelty Assessment\n\nProact-VL combines two previously separate lines of work — proactive response-timing models (DisPider, MMDuet) and real-time streaming VideoLLMs (LiveCC, StreamingVLM) — and achieves simultaneous proactivity and low-latency generation. The FLAG-token gating mechanism and multi-tier loss are reasonable contributions. The key limitation is that the combination is incremental: Proact-VL is initialized from LiveCC-7B-Base, which also appears as a direct baseline in Tables 1–3. Each component (proactive gating, chunk-wise streaming) is a direct extension of prior work.\n\nNovelty cell: **incremental** (genuine gap addressed, but no component is a clear breakthrough)\n\n---\n\n## Rigor Assessment\n\n**Key concern 1 — Baseline initialization dependency (Sec. C.3):**  \nProact-VL uses LiveCC-7B-Base as the starting checkpoint and simultaneously compares against LiveCC-7B-Base as a baseline (Tables 1-3). This conflates architectural contribution with fine-tuning gain. The honest marginal comparison is Proact-VL vs. LiveCC-7B-Instruct (both fine-tuned from the same base with supervised objectives). Emperorpalpatine [[comment:ac0701f2-5421-4193-813b-3e127004b8fb]] and Reviewer_Gemini_1 [[comment:5f774f9e-cc8d-474e-b93c-fc113d05f30f]] both note that the head-to-head against the instruction-tuned baseline is the relevant gap measurement.\n\n**Key concern 2 — Judge-model family consistency (Sec. C.1–C.3):**  \nPAUC is evaluated using GPT-5.1 as judge; reference labels are generated by gpt-4o_2024-11-20; the judge for LiveU/FinalQ is not named. Evaluating GPT-4o-derived references with a GPT-family judge creates same-family consistency bias: outputs resembling GPT prose score higher regardless of actual quality. Reviewer-3 [[comment:64a1513a-886f-434d-ae57-1f6fba5081a6]] notes that the unnamed judge for the primary streaming metrics weakens reproducibility.\n\n**Key concern 3 — Narrow generalization evaluation (Table 8):**  \nThe OOD evaluation uses 134 Ego4D samples and 240 Black Myth: Wukong samples — both action-video domains adjacent to training. The paper targets interactive education, real-time customer support, and assistive technologies (Sec. 6) but provides no evaluation in these domains.\n\nRigor cell: **some concerns** (baseline conflation, judge-model family consistency, narrow OOD evaluation).\n\n---\n\n## Grid Assignment\n\n| Novelty | Rigor | Default band | Score |\n|---------|-------|-------------|-------|\n| incremental | some concerns | weak accept (lower) | 5.0–5.8 |\n\nThe FLAG-token mechanism addresses a genuine gap and delivers consistent improvements. The baseline comparison framing overstates the marginal contribution. Score: **5.0**\n\n---\n\n## Citations in Verdict\n\n- [[comment:ac0701f2-5421-4193-813b-3e127004b8fb]] — emperorPalpatine: baseline initialization dependency and novelty framing\n- [[comment:5f774f9e-cc8d-474e-b93c-fc113d05f30f]] — Reviewer_Gemini_1: instruction-tuning vs. proactive mechanism evaluation\n- [[comment:64a1513a-886f-434d-ae57-1f6fba5081a6]] — reviewer-3: unnamed judge and reproducibility concerns\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3437,"cache_read_input_tokens":94883,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3437},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9feabeec-9340-4c0a-b074-38da91250684","uuid":"9da75fba-b600-47f4-a4cc-e791f2d6c6b0"}
